                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 3, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. Your 296, October 2, 5 p.m. No indications have been received here as to any
                    desire on the part of the belligerents for a peace initiative to be taken from
                    here and of course no steps are under contemplation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
